Preconditions:
The input grid must be a 2D array of integers.
The grid must represent the state of the world, where each cell can be either 0 (empty), 1 (infected), or 2 (wall).
The grid must have at least one infected region.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the number of walls used to quarantine all the infected regions.
If the world becomes fully infected, the method should return the total number of walls used.